What you need to know:

Dr. Raj Jutley, the Chief Medical Officer for the WRC Safari Rally, shared his plans and knowledge with the members of the Media Team on Sunday on the second day of the seminar held at Lake Naivasha ResortThe Paramedic Team will include over 40 ambulances, which will be supported by a further host of qualified doctors and team of medical expertsVera Dussausaye, the FIA Media Delegate, also briefed the members of the Press concerning their responsibility during the running of the Safari Rally in June